title: B-F racks up losses, but learns
text:
Buy Photo Bonduarant Farrar high school Bluejays (Photo: The Register) Buy Photo
CONNECT TWEET While the Bondurant-Farrar volleyball team may not have added a bunch of wins to their overall record, their journey to the state volleyball tournament continues undaunted.
“We knew going into this weekend we would play some of the best teams in the state,” said head coach Ray Sauer. “We played really well this week and it was a good growing experience.”
The Blue Jays started their week at Carroll on Tuesday and dropped a hard fought battle 22-25, 25-16, 21-25, and 26-28.
“They have become a big rival of ours,” Sauer said. “Our girls really played hard,” Jessica Noonan had 17 kills and was 12-13 serving. Alyssa Scheeler had 25 digs and was 16-17 serving. Devyn Atzen was 22-23 serving as well.
Saturday the Blue Jays travelled to perennial state-powerhouse Western-Christian of Hull for their tournament. Western Christian lived up to their reputation, defeating BF 21-4 and 21-13. Harlan was the second foe of the day and they dispatched BF 21-10 and 21-13. Logan Farmer had seven assists and was 4-4 serving. The Blue Jays were a perfect 24-24 serving in the match.
The third match of the day saw BF drop a 21-12, 13-21, and 13-15 contest to Sioux City, East. Farmer had 20 assists and was 12-12 serving. Sioux Falls O’Gorman (SD) defeated the Blue Jays in the fourth match 21-19, 21-9. Noonan had five kills and Connor Gauch had four.
In the final match, BF knocked off MOC-Floyd Valley 21-10, 21-16. Farmer again led the team in assists with 16 and was 6-7 serving. Abbey Burris had a nice serving match, going 11-13 with three aces.
“We played a lot of great teams, we played hard and learned a lot,” said Sauer, reviewing the week.
The Blue Jays (14-12) will host A-D-M Tuesday before travelling to Boone on Thursday. BF will wrap their week up with a tournament in Johnston.
